Date: Wed, 17 Dec 2025 12:07:58 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] Remove check-duplicate-ip6 from if-up.d installation
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Duplicate address checks for IPv6 are already handled externally by the
system through kernel-managed mechanisms. Since these validations are
already in place, installing an additional if-up script becomes
redundant. Removing this script avoids duplicated checks and keeps the
behavior aligned with the kernelâ€™s native IPv6 address validation.

Signed-off-by: Ferdinando Terada <ferdinando.godoyterada@windriver.com>
---
 debian/rules | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/debian/rules b/debian/rules
index 32ae425..93c492c 100755
--- a/debian/rules
+++ b/debian/rules
@@ -20,7 +20,6 @@ override_dh_install:
 	# Network scripts for ifupdown
 	install -m755 if-up-scripts/check-network-cable  $(CURDIR)/debian/ifupdown-extra/etc/network/if-up.d/00check-network-cable
 	install -m755 if-up-scripts/check-duplicate-ip  $(CURDIR)/debian/ifupdown-extra/etc/network/if-up.d/10check-duplicate-ip
-	install -m755 if-up-scripts/check-duplicate-ip6  $(CURDIR)/debian/ifupdown-extra/etc/network/if-up.d/10check-duplicate-ip6
 	install -m755 if-up-scripts/static-routes  $(CURDIR)/debian/ifupdown-extra/etc/network/if-up.d/20static-routes
 	install -m755 if-up-scripts/check-gateway  $(CURDIR)/debian/ifupdown-extra/etc/network/if-up.d/30check-gateway
 	# Serviced Unit file
